<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1926-06-15T15:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1926-06-15T15:00:00-05:00" n="67" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d67">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">800.51 W 89France/321: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Herrick</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1926-06-15T16:00:00-04:00"><hi rend="italic">June 15,
                                        1926—4 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>174. Referring to your telegram 224 of June 4, 11 a.m., information of
                            the Department is that the order placing an embargo against Boue Soeurs
                            was revoked June 8.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Kellogg</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>